The war in the Northeastern United States-- The epidemic's Gone East and West

By Kikuko

This morning work is not going well, a lot of things stuck, waiting for all the smooth process, see more news and Wechat, the mood is particularly heavy.

1. Numbers

Since January, day after day staring at the number, and finally watched it drop bit by bit, originally thought that since then clouds bright, Qingtai Ping, which know this plague still spread throughout the world. To date, nearly two hundred and fifty thousand people worldwide have fallen ill (242,190) . About 80,000 patients live in China, and one hundred and sixty thousand live abroad, twice as many as in China. The death toll in China is 3,253, with a total of 6,581 deaths outside the country, twice as many as at home.

South Korea, Japan, Singapore seem to be calming down, but Italy is in the grip of an epidemic, and today, Italy has surpassed China in the number of deaths.

https://coronavirus.jhu.edu/map.html

Total deaths worldwide: 10,030

Italy: 3,405 deaths

China: 3,253 deaths

Iran: 1,284 deaths

France: 372 deaths

United Kingdom: 137 deaths

South Korea: 94 deaths

An Iranian friend, Ali, wrote that their situation was so desperate that it was estimated that some three million Iranians would die when the plague was over. Iran's population is about eighty-four million, and he said 3.5 percent, which doesn't seem so inconceivable. Still, it's hard to imagine: Three million.

As of March 19, there were 13,150 infections and 196 deaths in the U.S. Then the governor announced the statewide lock down, saying that within eight weeks, 56 percent of Californians would be infected. There are twenty-five million, five hundred thousand people in California, more than one thousand, two hundred and seventy if half are infected. I really hope he's trying to scare the daredevils in Hollywood.

But these abstract numbers, they don't seem so scary. Even scarier are the specific people behind the numbers. Seven members of an Italian family in New Jersey have fallen ill, and four have died.

Grace FUSCO, 73, has 11 children and a great Italian mother. When she died on Wednesday night, March 18, she had no idea that one of her sons and daughters had died before her. After she left, another child died with her. Now, three more are dying in the hospital.

Do you remember the Chang-kai family.

https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/18/nyregion/new-jersey-family-coronavirus.html

The other grace, the goddess of so many, Grace Mariah Carey, the elegant and charming goddess of Hollywood's Golden Age, has long since left us, leaving behind a prince, the Albert II of Monaco, and Grace's son sick, positive.

The Massachusetts numbers, which I'm afraid to look at, are 328, which is a small number compared to two hundred and fifty thousand, but each number is followed by a familiar number of towns and cities around Boston, the plague is creeping in.

However, yesterday in a muddle to join the "mutual help" group, today understand its significance: it is to prevent the outbreak of the plague, was violent robbery, Chinese on Wechat to save each other. When I saw a group of friends posting a call to arms from a group in Los Angeles, I saw the signs of a local group: These groups are called "mutual aid" groups. Mutual aid means that someone runs to the door of the house and robs it, and then everyone calls for help. More than that, a group of gun owners were talking about gun classics. What gun sellers like most is the mass panic of such groups, which always makes guns and ammunition sell in large quantities. Sure enough, "the American nation is at its most dangerous moment. " Everyone is self-conscious, and guns are everywhere, somebody's GONNA knock on my closet door with the toilet paper and the 30-pound can of oil and the 50-pound bag of rice.

I understand the panic, I don't want to call it an overreaction, I don't want to blame the gun owners for trying to sell and enrich the nation, I'm not interested in the panic, the numbness, the panic, the nonchalance, the response is all about understanding and compassion: when the chips are down, let us each choose our own way of expressing our feelings.

New York is so empty, too

2. Family back home

Domestic figures have finally come down, from top to bottom, from the official to the people, are celebrating the big duck egg. The usual routine of going to work, getting on the train, being bold, and eating out in restaurants is now a luxury, and once it's back, it's precious.

They enjoy it while someone else worries about the numbers, it doesn't matter if everything is marked as zero in the media, but if you think about it, those Zeros can be reversed. Let's hope someone's still controlling these monsters.

Father is still in the hospital, yesterday and his video, usually the old father is always proud to walk, previously in the domestic hospital, but to see him lying in bed is the first time. They said he was going to be all right, and I believed he was going to be all right, and the hospital had treated hundreds of new patients, and now most of those people are out of the hospital, and some are gone forever, and the rest have been transferred to other hospitals. With them gone, the hospital will be able to admit ordinary patients like my father. Immediately, as soon as the ban is lifted, more ordinary patients will return to the hospital to treat and recuperate their illnesses for which they have not been treated or recuperated for two months.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Two-year-old children, innocent, just learned to express their thoughts and feelings in words, is the most mischievous and unreasonable age, English called "Terrible two" , in the epidemic two-year-old children but ahead of time, grandma to go to work, doll locked eyebrows, worried said: "The baby is very worried, AH, " adults told him, can go out to play, he said not to go out, "there is a virus. ".

The Spring Festival is a time for receiving red envelopes and gifts. The two-year-old doll did not receive red envelopes or the solemn gifts bought by all the people who love him. From the video, over and over again, he looked at the beautiful excavator bought for him, mouth watering, during the blockade, between the district and the end of the world, his excavator, but only look at the video thirst, still can not get. Wuhan is clear of zero, I hope he can be brave to go out the door, from his young mind to clear all the memories of the virus, free to take the bus, Light Rail, subway, ferry, running and jumping carefree in the city and streets that belong to him, walking freely in the city's high-rise buildings, shops, restaurants and hotels, in every park, in every green field, on the banks of the Han River, on the banks of the East L. River, and then, finally, get their own long-coveted golden brilliant excavator.

3. In sickness and in health, there is no such thing as a light weight

With regard to Ms. Li of Biogen, both at home and abroad, in Chinese and English, she has been subjected to meticulous investigation, human flesh and merciless whipping. I do not in the least deny or trivialize the immense threat and immeasurable harm she poses to the public. She must be punished by the law and condemned by morality. I have no right or intention to defend her.

However, after witnessing the great panic and the real death and pain of the past two months and more, I felt both compassion for her. This plague, a plague that fell from the sky and robbed her of the life she had fought so hard for, under normal circumstances, no matter how selfish, how narrow, how fearful of death, how reckless of merit, how many tiny words were hidden under her fur robe, on the ordinary life orbit, how many opportunities let it expose in the public, for the society, others and oneself cause irretrievable loss? The choices she made in the Live and Let Die cost her everything she was -- a life of success, career, money, status, identity, and no place to hide, not in China, not in the United States.

At the same time, she, her husband and, it seems, her son were still fighting the disease. In other words, she has to fight off the virus before she can be judged legally and morally.

I dare not condemn her too forcefully, for I do not know what choice I would make if I were in her position. I hope we never have to face that choice.

Usually the so-called child of Heaven, in the domestic school and foreign workplace smooth water, suddenly facing the most essential thing of life, life and death, I feel, she is like a little mouse performing on the stage, the stage was originally dark lamp, then suddenly the lights came on and the little mouse was caught in the light. Under the suddenly bright light, some mice were frightened to flee around, some mice were shocked to stay in place, not calm, but scared silly. You don't know where the lights will come on, and it's just a fluke that you're lucky to stay in the dark.

In the face of sudden disaster, who can say that we are not only running around or in place of the little mouse. It could be any one of us.

4. Birthdays and celebrations

March, is a very important month in our family, there are two people's birthday, this year would like to celebrate with great fanfare, but have been forced into a small family within the underground activities.

No Birthday Party, no graduation ceremony, children suddenly grow up, but did not have time to leave a milestone.

The good news is that America is only now beginning to shut down, that college admissions have already begun, and that even if they work remotely, all that's left is a head count. He didn't make it to the top of his wish list, but he did get a couple of good Accepted. Hoping to be content, smug, nose in the air with him as he strolled through the schools that had accepted him, and then finally deciding which one to go to, this year seemed hopeless, with so few important pages missing from his photo album.

We are content, birthday however, the years still continue to flow forward, no graduation ceremony, there are still books to read below, there is school to go.

And many of the jobs, industries, and businesses that are already about to disappear might, if all goes well, survive for a while before disappearing altogether. Once the epidemic came, the good wind by force, sent me to the clouds, the bad wind by force, sent Iraq under the mire, this is more devastating, will never come back. Helplessly see helpless flowers fall, do not expect deja Vu Yan Return.

It's the first day of spring. Birthday's tomorrow. Happy Birthday.

The wife of an Indian colleague is about to have a baby. Today, I realized that he has no sense of protection, nor any protective equipment. I gave him some of the face mask, hand sanitizer and hand sanitizer I had in my hand. I decided to give him all of them since I was buying them elsewhere. I can not and will not participate in large-scale fund-raising and donation activities, to the lack of colleagues to send a little urgently needed supplies, it is I made a small contribution to the fight against the epidemic.
